# AutoResearcher Skills

When the user asks about running experiments, training models, or managing ML research, invoke the appropriate skill below.

## Available Skills

| Command | When to Use |
|---------|-------------|
| `/auto-experiment` | User wants to start autonomous 24/7 experiment loop |
| `/code-review` | User wants architecture review before training |
| `/code-cleanup` | User wants to clean up obsolete code |
| `/experiment-status` | User asks about experiment progress |
| `/gpu-monitor` | User asks about GPU status |
| `/idea-validation` | User wants to validate a research idea |
| `/model-architect` | User wants to design a new model architecture |
| `/paper-research` | User wants to find relevant papers |
| `/paper-analyze` | User wants deep analysis of a paper |
| `/dataset-understanding` | User wants to understand dataset structure |
| `/error-handler` | Experiment failed, user wants diagnosis |
| `/progress-report` | User wants a progress report |

## Programmatic Usage

```python
from api import AutoResearcher

# Initialize for a project
r = AutoResearcher("/path/to/project")

# Run one cycle
result = r.run_one_cycle()

# Get status
status = r.get_status()

# Start background daemon
pid = r.start_daemon(gpu="0", max_cycles=10)
r.stop_daemon()

# Query learned lessons
lessons = r.get_code_review_lessons(severity="HIGH")
```

## CLI Usage

```bash
# Status
python api.py status --project /path/to/project

# Run 3 cycles
python api.py run --project /path/to/project --cycles 3

# Start daemon
python api.py start --project /path/to/project --gpu 0

# Stop daemon
python api.py stop

# Show learned lessons
python api.py lessons --project /path/to/project --severity HIGH
```

## Project Requirements

The project directory must contain:
1. `PROJECT_BRIEF.md` — describes research goal, codebase, constraints
2. `config.yaml` (optional) — agent configuration
3. Python training scripts

## Skill Files Location

Skill definitions are in `skills/<name>/SKILL.md`. When invoking a skill, read the corresponding SKILL.md file and follow its instructions.
